<p>We set the scrutiny start date, being the start date of the calculation and the end date of the scrutiny period.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L18' title='View on GitHub'>18</a>         @scrutiny_start_date = nil</code></pre>
<p>We go forward one day.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L21' title='View on GitHub'>21</a>         date = date.next</code></pre>
<p>We set the day count to zero.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L24' title='View on GitHub'>24</a>         day_count = 0</code></pre>
<h2>Whilst the number of days we’re counting is less than the target number of days to count ...</h2>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L27' title='View on GitHub'>27</a>         while day_count &lt; target_day_count</code></pre>
<p>... we continue to the <strong>previous day</strong>.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L30' title='View on GitHub'>30</a>           date = date.prev_day</code></pre>
<p>If the day is a scrutiny day in both Houses ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L33' title='View on GitHub'>33</a>           if date.is_joint_scrutiny_day?</code></pre>
<p>... we set the scrutiny start date to this date if the scrutiny start date is nil ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L36' title='View on GitHub'>36</a>             @scrutiny_start_date = date if @scrutiny_start_date.nil?</code></pre>
<p>... and add 1 to the day count.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/bicameral_both_houses_sitting.rb#L39' title='View on GitHub'>39</a>             day_count += 1</code></pre>
<p>Otherwise, if the calendar has no record of what type of day this is, we can&#39;t calculate the end date, ...</p>

